"""
# Variant API Parity Specification

**Feature IDs:** #VAP-001
**Category:** Stdlib
**Difficulty:** 2/5
**Status:** In Progress
**Requirements:** doc/requirement/variant_api_parity.md
**Plan:** doc/03_plan/variant_api_parity.md
**Design:** N/A
**Research:** N/A

## Overview

Verifies that gc_async_mut, nogc_async_mut, and nogc_sync_mut expose equivalent
public APIs for shared modules: torch (Tensor, ops, optim), gpu (GpuArray,
Context, device), gpu_runtime, and ptr.

## Key Concepts

| Concept | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| API Parity | All 3 variants export the same public functions/methods for shared modules |
| Ownership Difference | GC uses owns_handle, NoGC uses unconditional drop - this is by design |
| Shared Module | A module (cuda, gpu, torch) that exists in all 3 variants |
"""

# @req VAP-001
# @feature variant_api_parity
# @tag:system

